<P>
   (Eds: ETA 3 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   with YELTSIN-LEGACY-0101 _ MOSCOW _ President Boris Nikolayevich
Yeltsin flirted with greatness in leading his country out of the
communist wilderness, helped topple the Soviet Union and went on to
become the first popularly elected leader in 1,000 years of Russian
history. Yet he ended his career in frustration and sad irony
without assuring its stable future. (Holmes, Cox Washington Bureau)
</P>
<P>
   (Eds: ETA 3 p.m.)
</P>
