   RUSSIA-YELTSIN (Moscow) _ Boris Yeltsin resigns as president,
saying, ``Russia must enter the new millennium with new
politicians, with new faces, with new, smart, strong, energetic
people.'' Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, Yeltsin's chosen successor
who is riding high in the polls, becomes acting president (under
the Constitution). A presidential election will be held in 90 days,
instead of in June as scheduled. By Celestine Bohlen.
