understood as 1900, rather than 2thout repairs, that
seemingly simple problem could cause equipment to malfunction.
</P>
<P>
   Koskinen said Friday that U. S. taxpayers have spent about $8.5
billion fixing federal computers. Private industry has spent
another $100 billion. And perhaps another $200 billion has been
spent collectively by other countries.
