 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   FRANCE: EXPLOSIVES LINKED TO BASQUES SEIZED
</P>
<P>
   The French police have seized a ton of explosives they said
belonged to the Spanish Basque separatist guerrilla group ETA, a
week after two powerful van bombs were found and defused in Spain.
The explosives were found in an unused garage outside the city of
Pau near the Spanish border.
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA: LEADER KILLS GENOCIDE BILL
</P>
<P>
   In an unexpected reversal, President Andres Pastrana vetoed a
bill that would have made genocide and forced disappearance
criminal acts. His administration shifted course after the armed
forces complained that such a law would leave soldiers open to
prosecution, in civilian rather than military courts, for deaths
inflicted in combat with leftist guerrillas.
</P>
