</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DOW-YEAREND01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    It was a very, very good year on Wall Street
 &HT;    By Tom Walker
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The longest bull market in history showed no signs of
letup Friday as the major stock averages ended the 20th century at
record highs. The day's action rounded out a year that gave
investors an unprecedented fifth straight year of double-digit
gains.
