jumped from 5 million to 64 million. The number of cars registered
in the country grew from 8,000 to 207 million. The number of farms
dropped by more than half. And the percentage of American homes
with VCRs went from 0 to 83.
</P>
<P>
   All that in a century's time. All that in a tenth of a
millennium.
</P>
