</P>
<P>
   We have done good and we have done evil.
</P>
<P>
   We can do better.
</P>
<P>
   And so, this morning, when change is in the air, let's revive a
slogan from the last century and say, with relief, Goodbye to all
that. Let's remember that, after spending so much time getting
here, we finally have survived and arrived, and that today is
tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(David M. Shribman is chief of The Globe's Washington bureau.)
</P>
</TEXT>
