   Y2K-RDP (Undated) _ The world's computers suffered a few
sputters and glitches, but they seem to have survived the Year 2000
rollover with no evidence yet of severe problems that had once been
feared. The real test, experts say, will come in the days and weeks
ahead as people return to work, factories start up and stores open
their doors. But the rush of recent months to fix the Year 2000
problem, and spending of more than $250 billion, may well have paid
off. Developing. By Steve Lohr.
