   RUSSIA-YELTSIN (Moscow) _ President Boris Yeltsin shocked his
nation and the world Friday by announcing his resignation six
months before the end of his term, and handed over power to his
favored successor, Prime Minister Vladimir Putin. As final act to
an extraordinary career, Yeltsin, 68, chose the last day of the
year and the start of a four-day New Year's holiday in Russia to
upstage the new milennium, and try to assert control over a
succession battle that will set Russia's course for years to come.
By Celestine Bohlen.
