hijackers sped off in waiting cars today with two Islamic militants
and a Muslim cleric released from Indian jails and were given 10
hours to find freedom, ending a tense eight-day standoff in
Afghanistan. All 155 hostages on the Indian Airlines plane were
freed unharmed. (summary from wires) By Celia W. Dugger.
</P>
