<HEADLINE>
PSYCHIC SAYS: CHAN EXITS, NORV ENTERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GIL LEBRETON 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   When your noble soothsayer peered into the coming year in the
world of sports, I saw clouds. I saw flashes of great lightning. I
heard Ricky Martin music and I couldn't turn down the volume.
</P>
<P>
   How was I to know that the crystal ball wasn't Y2K] ready?
</P>
<P>
   But fear not. The old ball is back in service and ready to
predict the year 2000's sportly happenings.
</P>
<P>
   It's all going to be true, just as my prediction was last year
(ahem) that the Stars would beat Buffalo in overtime of Game 6 to
win the Stanley Cup. (Insert gasps of amazement here).
</P>
<P>
   Read, therefore, and gaze with wonder: January Fourth-quarter
scoring run by Hodges Mitchell gives suspension-depleted Texas a
24-21 victory over Arkansas in Cotton Bowl ... Nebraska defense
smothers QB Tee Martin and Cornhuskers prevail over Tennessee,
21-10, in Fiesta ... Peter Warrick catches two TD passes and
Sebastian Janikowski kicks three field goals as Florida State
outclasses Virginia Tech, 30-20, in Sugar Bowl ... In Y2K computer
glitch, national title awarded to Marshall . . . Late field goal by
Eddie Murray gives Cowboys 13-10 win over New York Giants and earns
playoff berth ... In first-round wild card game, Jeff George and
Vikings stagger Cowboys, 34-6 ... Jimmy Smith catches winning TD
pass as Jacksonville outlasts Peyton Manning and Colts, 35-31, to
win AFC title ... In NFC championship game, Minnesota too much for
St. Louis Rams, 28-17 ... Rangers continue homecoming party, ink
left-hander Darren Oliver ... Nicolas Lapentti beats Andre Agassi
in finals of Australian Open. Lindsay Davenport captures women's
crown ... James Stewart runs for 110 yards and three touchdowns as
Jaguars win Super Bowl XXXIV over Vikings, 24-20 ... Chan Gailey
resigns as Cowboys head coach.
February Norv Turner, fired in Washington, named to replace Gailey
as Cowboys coach ... Michael Finley selected to West squad for NBA
All-Star Game ... Mike Modano, Ed Belfour, Brett Hull and Sergei
Zubov selected to NHL All-Star Game ... Tony Stewart wins Daytona
500 ... Twenty snowboarders forget way to marijuana testing lab and
declared ineligible at Winter X Games ... George Dunham hound ``Bo
Jackson'' selected Best in Drooling at annual Westminster Dog Show
... Italy's Prada sails past Russell Coutts' Team New Zealand to
win America's Cup.
March TCU finishes 20-12, but snubbed by NCAA basketball tourney
selectors ... New Dale Hansen swimming pool joins Great Wall of
China as only manmade structures visible from Space Shuttle ...
Frogs knock off Southern Miss in first round of NIT but are
eliminated in second-round loss at Arizona State ... Mickey
Spagnola, the Sicilian Sharpshooter, scores twice but Team Hardline
regains KTCK Charity Challenge on Ice crown in front of 17,001 at
Reunion Arena ... Stanford, Duke, Connecticut and Indiana make
men's Final Four ... On eve of baseball opener, Seattle Mariners
trade Ken Griffey Jr. to Cincinnati Reds for pitcher Scott
Williamson, shortstop Travis Dawkins and outfielder Adam Dunn ...
