radio personality Randy Galloway turns down three-year,
$22.5-million offer to jump to KLIF/570. Galloway says he doesn't
need the money ... Stars finish regular season with 42-32-8 record,
then eliminate St. Louis Blues in first round of NHL playoffs ...
Mavericks conclude NBA season with 29-53 record ... Owner Ross
Perot Jr. announces that Don Nelson will return as head coach.
Season ticket sales plummet.
</P>
<P>
   May Justin Thompson throws four-hit shutout in debut with
Rangers, beating Mariners ... More Than Ready wins 126th running of
Kentucky Derby ... Justin Leonard triumphs at Byron Nelson Golf
Classic ... Duffy Waldorf takes Colonial NIT ... Stars outlast
Phoenix Coyotes in seven games to advance to NHL Western Conference
finals ... Professor Craig Miller of KTCK radio among 13 named in
NCAA phony degree scandal ... Cowboys receiver Michael Irvin
announces retirement from pro football ... First-day stock soars as
noted colleague Jim Reeves opens revo.com website, specializing in
Nolan Ryan memorabilia ... Pat Verbeek scores winning goal in
overtime of Game 6 as Detroit Red Wings dethrone Stars in
